  "local_port": 43086,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some locations in Tennessee that are suitable for a prom?",
  "response": "Planning a prom involves selecting a venue that provides the right ambiance, adequate space, and necessary amenities to ensure a memorable event for students. Tennessee offers a variety of excellent locations across its cities that cater to different themes and sizes of prom gatherings. Here are some top venues in Tennessee suitable for hosting a prom:\n\n### **Nashville**\n\n1. **The Bell Tower**\n   - **Description:** A sophisticated event space in downtown Nashville, known for its elegant architecture and versatile rooms.\n   - **Features:** Grand ballrooms, state-of-the-art lighting and sound systems, customizable decor options, and catering services.\n   - **Capacity:** Suitable for both small and large gatherings.\n\n2. **The Nashville Shores Lakeside Resort & Waterpark**\n   - **Description:** Combines indoor and outdoor spaces with scenic lake views, ideal for a unique prom experience.\n   - **Features:** Multiple event spaces, on-site accommodations, waterpark access, and diverse catering options.\n   - **Capacity:** Accommodates large groups, perfect for sizeable prom parties.\n\n3. **Cheekwood Estate & Gardens**\n   - **Description:** A historic estate with beautiful gardens and elegant indoor spaces, offering a picturesque setting.\n   - **Features:** Historic architecture, lush gardens for photo opportunities, and customizable event packages.\n   - **Capacity:** Suitable for medium to large events.\n\n### **Memphis**\n\n1. **Memphis Botanical Garden**\n   - **Description:** Offers lush landscapes and versatile indoor venues, providing a natural and elegant backdrop.\n   - **Features:** Beautiful gardens, greenhouse facilities, flexible seating arrangements, and catering partnerships.\n   - **Capacity:** Ideal for medium-sized prom events.\n\n2. **The Peabody Memphis Hotel**\n   - **Description:** A historic hotel renowned for its charm and high-quality event facilities.\n   - **Features:** Grand ballrooms, sophisticated decor, professional event planning services, and excellent dining options.\n   - **Capacity:** Can host both intimate and large-scale proms.\n\n3. **Bass Pro Shops at the Pyramid**\n   - **Description:** A unique and modern venue located within the iconic Memphis Pyramid, offering panoramic views of the Mississippi River.\n   - **Features:** Spacious event areas, contemporary design, advanced audiovisual equipment, and on-site catering.\n   - **Capacity:** Suitable for large prom gatherings.\n\n### **Knoxville**\n\n1. **Sage Pavilion at World's Fair Park**\n   - **Description:** An outdoor pavilion with stunning views of the park and skyline, perfect for an open-air prom.\n   - **Features:** Scenic surroundings, flexible space for decorations, and access to park amenities.\n   - **Capacity:** Ideal for medium to large events.\n\n2. **The James White Theatre**\n   - **Description:** A historic venue offering a blend of classic charm and modern facilities.\n   - **Features:** Elegant interiors, customizable lighting and sound, and professional event support.\n   - **Capacity:** Suitable for medium-sized proms.\n\n3. **Boulevard Club and Ballroom**\n   - **Description:** Located in downtown Knoxville, offering a luxurious setting with modern amenities.\n   - **Features:** Spacious ballrooms, high-end decor, state-of-the-art audiovisual systems, and on-site catering.\n   - **Capacity:** Can accommodate large prom parties.\n\n### **Chattanooga**\n\n1. **The Tivoli Theatre**\n   - **Description:** A historic theater with ornate architecture and a grand stage, providing a dramatic and elegant setting.\n   - **Features:** Vintage charm, customizable seating arrangements, and professional lighting and sound systems.\n   - **Capacity:** Suitable for medium to large events.\n\n2. **The Cove**\n   - **Description:** A modern event space with versatile layouts, perfect for themed proms and contemporary celebrations.\n   - **Features:** Open floor plans, modern decor options, advanced audiovisual equipment, and catering services.\n   - **Capacity:** Accommodates both small and large groups.\n\n3. **Chattanooga Convention Center**\n   - **Description:** A large, flexible venue capable of hosting significant events with ample space and modern facilities.\n   - **Features:** Multiple event halls, customizable setups, comprehensive support services, and diverse catering options.\n   - **Capacity:** Ideal for very large prom gatherings.\n\n### **Other Notable Locations in Tennessee**\n\n- **The Putnam House in Franklin:** A historic mansion offering elegant indoor and outdoor spaces, perfect for a traditional or vintage-themed prom.\n- **Beale Park Pavilion in Jackson:** A versatile outdoor venue with beautiful park surroundings, suitable for larger, nature-inspired proms.\n- **The Parthenon in Nashville:** Offers a unique architectural backdrop inspired by the original Parthenon in Athens, ideal for a themed prom.\n\n### **Considerations When Choosing a Venue**\n\n1. **Capacity:** Ensure the venue can comfortably accommodate your entire guest list.\n2. **Location:** Choose a location that is easily accessible for all attendees, considering transportation and parking facilities.\n3. **Ambiance and Theme:** Select a venue that aligns with your desired prom theme, whether it's classic, modern, outdoor, or themed.\n4. **Budget:** Factor in the cost of the venue, including any additional services like catering, decoration, and entertainment.\n5. **Amenities:** Consider what the venue offers in terms of lighting, sound systems, dance floors, and other essential amenities.\n6. **Availability:** Popular venues can book up quickly, so it's crucial to secure your preferred location well in advance.\n\nBy evaluating these factors and exploring the venues listed above, you can find the perfect location in Tennessee to host a memorable and enjoyable prom event.",
